  "snippet": "Hi Alex, Thank you for submitting your project. I&#39;ve now had a chance to review it in detail and wanted to share some feedback that I hope you&#39;ll find useful. What went well • You demonstrate a",
  "body": "Hi Alex,\n\nThank you for submitting your project. I’ve now had a chance to review it in detail and wanted to share some feedback that I hope you’ll find useful.\n\nWhat went well\n• You demonstrate a solid grasp of the core course concepts and apply them effectively.\n• Your data analysis is carefully executed and the statistical methods are appropriate.\n• The visualizations you included are clear, well-labeled, and do a great job of supporting your conclusions.\n• Your writing is generally clear and the overall structure of the paper makes it easy to follow your argument.\n\nAreas to strengthen\n• Hypothesis focus – Your hypothesis is interesting, but it’s stated a bit broadly. Sharpening it into a more concise, specific statement will help readers see exactly what you set out to test and why it matters.\n• Research question alignment – Once you tighten the hypothesis, double-check that every section of the paper clearly points back to it. This will make the narrative even more compelling.\n\nOverall assessment\nThe project earns a solid B+. This reflects the strong analytical work and presentation, while also indicating that there’s room to refine the framing of your study. With a more precise hypothesis and tighter alignment between sections, this could easily move into the A range.\n\nNext steps\nIf you’d like to discuss any of these points in more depth or talk about ways to revise the project for future use (e.g., conference or portfolio submission), let me know and we can set up a time to chat.\n\nThanks again for your hard work on this—well done!\n\nBest,\n[Your Name]\n"
}","annotations":null}

